 common cash flow management mistakes. Keep reading to gain insight.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"what-is-cash-flow\"><\/span>What is Cash Flow?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Cash flow is the money that comes in and out of your business at a certain period. There are two types of cash flow:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 <strong>Positive Cash Flow<\/strong>&#8211; this is when more money is coming into the business compared to what you are spending.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 <strong>Negative cash flow<\/strong>&#8211; is when more money in your business is used than what is getting into the company. It is a sign that you will have trouble paying future business expenses.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Your business should always have enough cash flow to meet all future obligations. This is why it is vital to practice managing cash flow in the organization. It significantly helps in avoiding the pitfalls.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"why-is-business-cash-flow-important\"><\/span>Why is Business Cash Flow Important?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Without cash, your business cannot exist. This is because it is the lifeblood of your company, meaning it can either make the business grow or die. According to the Harvard Business Review, most people agree that business growth requires investment. It means cash must be present in a company for progress to happen.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If there is limited or no money at hand, most likely, your business will not work out. But if you have the right amount of money, your job is to figure out how to manage cash flow. Think of how to grow a healthy organization and increase profit margins.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"best-cash-flow-management-practices\"><\/span>Best Cash Flow Management Practices<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"understand-business-cash-flow\"><\/span>Understand Business Cash Flow<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The first thing you should do is to understand the cash movements in the business. You should know that there is a huge difference between profits and cash flow. The profit of your business is the revenue you receive minus the expenses and tax.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If you <a href=\"https:\/\/www.bakertilly.com\/insights\/best-practices-in-cash-management\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">do not understand this concept<\/a>, business finance solutions will help you. They may assist you in creating cash flow forecasts and statements to help you track cash movements.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"boost-your-sales-not-the-expenses\"><\/span>Boost Your Sales, Not the Expenses<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When using cash, ensure it is for a valid reason. Otherwise, unnecessary expenses can cause the business to strain. Your sales should always be more than your expenses. This will significantly improve the business in the long run.<br>Take advantage of business finance solutions. Many of them guide businesses on how to spend money and increase profits.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"assist-your-customers\"><\/span>Assist your customers<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Having customers in your business is very important as they generate cash flow. As a small business owner, you should help your customers purchase what they want successfully.<br>Completing a financial transaction can sometimes be challenging for customers. This is why you should help your customers to avoid incomplete checkouts.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"plan-your-growth\"><\/span>Plan Your Growth<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Having a strategic plan is the key to any successful business. Ensure that you do things systematically to avoid sabotaging other parts of the company. For example, do not invest in some equipment too early. Do your timing well and know when is the right time to make progress.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/cashflow-management-practices-business-finance-solutions-1.jpg\" alt=\"business finance solutions\" class=\"wp-image-567\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/cashflow-management-practices-business-finance-solutions-1.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/cashflow-management-practices-business-finance-solutions-1-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/12\/cashflow-management-practices-business-finance-solutions-1-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"cash-flow-management-mistakes-business-owners-should-know\"><\/span>Cash Flow Management Mistakes Business Owners Should Know<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Not Using the Right Management Tools<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are several cash flow management tools to use to boost your business. They will help you plan the business from scratch, and you will also know how to allocate your money.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Financial services as Management tools<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Business finance solutions don&#8217;t just come in the form of management tools. Financial services can also act as tools to help your business grow. Loans, bank accounts, mortgages, and credit cards are a few examples of financial services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, you can use bank accounts to save and distribute business funds to avoid confusion. Verv bank accounts are great to use for your business as they offer safe, reliable, and fast transactions. The company offers two types of accounts;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong><a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/business-account\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\">Business Account<\/a>;<\/strong> you can use the Verv business account to settle various payments and purchase equipment instantly. They also offer payment gateways to company owners.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Personal Account<\/strong>; Verv personal account can also be of help. You can open an account for your employees to pay them with ease.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Not Preparing for Worse Times<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>If something unexpected arises, it might cause your business to fail. This is why you should always have money saved up in case of anything. Even though it will not help boost the business, it will maintain its current level. In this case, business finance solutions can help.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Not monitoring the inventory<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>When sales decrease, it will create an impact on the business cash flow. Businesses must have a closer look at the company\u2019s inventory to make timely decisions. For example, they can know when to get their goods at better prices.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"reports-that-help-cfos-maintain-cash-flow\"><\/span>Reports That Help CFOs Maintain Cash Flow<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Five main financial reports help CFOs in managing cash flow. You can also implement them in your business as they may help in avoiding the pitfalls. Here they are;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Income Statement<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This statement indicates the profits and losses of a company over a specific time.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Balance Sheet<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>This is an important report that many organizations usually overlook. It shows you how funds have been generated and used.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Working Capital Report<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Working capital is the money that is available to the business for daily activities. The reports are usually prepared weekly.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>Sales Analysis Report<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The sale analysis report is what many businesses review daily. It shows the number of sales in a day and how the company is performing.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"why-consider-cash-flow-management-practices\"><\/span>Why Consider Cash Flow Management Practices?<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Cash flow management practices help businesses grow and track performance. Companies can use business finance solutions like Verv bank accounts to increase business efficiency. Use the above tips to maintain cash flow in your business.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Introduction One of the biggest reasons why most businesses fail is poor cash flow management. Cash flow is a critical factor when it comes to any business. Therefore, business owners must set proper management systems to ensure adequate cash flow in the company. It helps boost the business in case opportunities arise. Managing cash flow [&hellip;]<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":2,"featured_media":566,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[16],"tags":[],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/488"}],"collection":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/2"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=488"}],"version-history":[{"count":2,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/488\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":568,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/488\/revisions\/568"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/566"}